<item>
            <title>[LU-9395] hostlist_expand is wrongly used to expand simple number range</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9395</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;hostlist_expand is defined to expand hostlist, e.g. trevis-72vm&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2-5,7,9&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. But we wrongly use it to expand simple number range (ost indices) in test-framework.sh, e.g. &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2-5,7,9&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
For example, if you run the following test case in sanity.sh, &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;test_888() {
       echo &quot;test hostlist_expand&quot;
       hostlist_expand &quot;[3-7,9,10]&quot;
       hostlist_expand &quot;trevis-73vm[3-7,9,10]&quot;
}
run_test 888 &quot;test hostlist_expand&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;you will see the output is&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 888: test hostlist_expand == 16:34:03 (1493109243)
test hostlist_expand
4
trevis-73vm3 trevis-73vm4 trevis-73vm5 trevis-73vm6 trevis-73vm7 trevis-73vm9 trevis-73vm10
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
